I know I played with OnShape a few seasons ago and I know I still have an account somewhere on their network but I have been unable to access it with my personal email address. At some point, they enabled 2-Factor Authentication and I have no way to access a 2FA code through any of my authenticator apps or my physical auth key. I’ve tried regaining access by contacting their ‘Security’ team, I’ve used their general contact form and tried to sign up for a new educational account with the same email with no responses thus far and no luck with the new account. I have another non-work email account that I use to handle my personal accounts (bank, mortgage, etc.) that I would like to keep segregated but I guess I could use it if all else fails.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’m looking for anyone with any insider contacts to help restore my account so I can evaluate OnShape (again) for the 2024 season. At this point I don’t care if they have to wipe all data from my account, I didn’t have much in the first place. I know in the past DS SolidWorks had a liaison on these forums, I have to imagine there is someone of relative equivalency representing OnShape. Or someone could respond to my emails privately, a courtesy I have yet to receive even in the negative. I realize this is more of a personal issue but knowing that other teams may be transitioning soon I would hope that their process of gaining a new account or reopening an old one is
